replies.body:
Having an adaptive playstyle to play basically any role due to the meta constantly changing apparently takes no skills compared to being a one-trick pony and only playing one champion. It also takes skill to identify what IS good in a current meta which as stated above will primarily be assassins vs adcs for preseason by the looks of things. We did not pull that statement out of our ass but by inferring that adcs will be strong and multi-laned due to buffs and item changes and that Assassins will be needed to counter the ADCs. If you want to show off your 200k mastery point Sion or whatever for the sake of your mad skillz in a meta full of ADCs that will literally shred through your like you were made of paper mache (the irony is palpable) then you can go right ahead and lose because you are narrow-minded.

You make it sound like playing "meta" champions will not take any skill and that if I pick one I will automatically win. That is simply not the case since most of them do take a few brain cells or games under your belt to play well. Yasuo for one will be very strong in the preseason but you cannot expect a first time Yas to do well because he has a rather high skill cap to be able to carry the game all on his own. 

"Change is good." - {{champion:121}} 
"It's time for a true display of skill!" - {{champion:81}}
